TY  - JOUR
AU  - Belo, Frederico
AU  - Li, Jun
AU  - Lin, Xiaoji
AU  - Zhao, Xiaofei
T1  - Labor-Force Heterogeneity and Asset Prices: The Importance of Skilled Labor
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx070
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 10
SP  - 3669
EP  - 3709
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Previous studies have identified a negative relation between firms’ hiring rates and future stock returns in the cross-section. We document that this relation is significantly steeper in industries that rely relatively more on high-skill workers than low-skill workers. A long-short portfolio sorted on firm-level hiring rate earns an average annual return of 8.6% in high-skill industries, and only 0.9% in low-skill industries. Moreover, this pattern is not explained by the standard CAPM. These findings are consistent with a neoclassical model with labor force heterogeneity and labor market frictions if it is more costly to replace high-skill than low-skill workers.Received August 14, 2015; editorial decision December 31, 2016 by Editor Leonid Kogan.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx070
ER  - 



