TY  - JOUR
AU  - Irani, Rustom M.
AU  - Meisenzahl, Ralf R.
T1  - Loan Sales and Bank Liquidity Management: Evidence from a U.S. Credit Register
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx024
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 10
SP  - 3455
EP  - 3501
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine how banks use loan sales to manage liquidity during periods of marketwide stress and the associated spillovers to market prices. We track the dynamics of loan share ownership in the secondary market using data from a U.S. supervisory register of syndicated loans. Controlling for loan quality using loan-year fixed effects, we find that banks reliant on wholesale funding were more likely to exit syndicates through sales during 2007/08. This effect is stronger for banks dependent on short-term funding and holding fewer liquid securities. In addition, secondary market prices decrease significantly more for loans funded by liquidity-strained banks.Received November 16, 2015; editorial decision January 9, 2017 by Editor Itay Goldstein.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx024
ER  - 



